    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72112/990½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to President
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I am sending you the telegram
                    drafted by Mr. Lansing.<note n="61" xml:id="d248fn1">Not printed; for the
                        telegram as sent, see <ref target="frus1915Supp#pg_152">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1915, supp., p.
                        152</ref>.</note> I have just had time to read it but not time to go over it
                    with a view to digesting it sentence by sentence. He has worked in nearly, if
                    not all of your language but the impression it makes upon me is that the tone of
                    it is a little more severe than the tone of your memorandum.<note n="62"
                        xml:id="d248fn2">Enclosure to President Wilson’s letter of Mar. 19, 1915,
                            <ref target="#pg_278">p. 278</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>If, after you have had an opportunity to consider it, you desire any exchange of
                    views I am at your service, as is Mr. Lansing.</p>
                <p>With assurances [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
